{
  "texts": [
    "They employed ten virtual markers to gather data on six facial emotions (happiness, sadness, anger, fear, disgust, and surprise).",
    "Additionally, 55 college students with a mean age of 22.9 years (35 male and 25 female) freely participated in the experiment for facial emotion identification.",
    "Additionally, 19 undergraduate students offered their services to gather EEG signals.",
    "For the first phase of facial and eye detection, Haar-like features are employed.",
    "Based on a facial action coding system, the Lucas-Kande optical flow method is then used to track the characteristics when virtual markers are later set in specific spots on the subject's face."
  ]
}